				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I always allocate the total number of bytes of multi-byte variables, and refer to the individual bytes by adding their indices to the base address (i.e. VariableName+0 is the first byte, VariableName+1 is the second byte, and so on). Adding 0 to the base address may look silly, but makes it clear that this is indeed the lowest byte of a multi-byte variable.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

